						               													<description>The Artillery Outpost &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; is a special double-tile terrain  supplement for Neuroshima Hex and Neroshima Hex: Babel13!. It was a promotion piece provided at Spiel 2008 and then added to the Neroshima Hex Babel13 expansion (only preorder).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; is a special terrain element. &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; covers two hexes. Place a Turret tile on one of the 2 hexes. &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; is armed with this Turret.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player occupies the second hex (the steering wheel) with a friendly unit, he can rotate the Turret during his turn. During a Battle the Turret does damage to every unit hit by it (no matter if its your or enemy unit).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Unit which steers &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; does not perform any other action during the battle. If the steering unit dies or leaves the hex, &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; is unoccupied. The next player who moves a Unit there will gain control of &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot;. If during a battle nobody controls &amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot;, the Turret attacks automatically in the direction it is aimed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;THUNDER&amp;quot; can not be destroyed; you can only kill the unit that controls it. Features as Terrain: Turret, Control Panel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Neuroshima Hex! 3.0&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
